		</div>
		<div class="comment-content" style="display:block;">

			<p>How about for policy options:<br />
1. how is immigration (both legal and illegal) affecting the US population?<br />
2. How is that population growth affecting the environmental sustainability of the US population? (Among other things, the average immigrant&#8217;s greenhouse emissions rise fourfold after arrival in the US&#8211;can we reduce emissions 80% by 2050 as per what global warming experts recommend if immigration continues unabated, or even rises drastically, as per the Senate bill?)</p>
<p>3. what is the impact of immigration on the wages and unemployment levels of working class Americans? Of white collar Americans?</p>
<p><a href="//cis.org/all-employment-growth-since-2000-went-to-immigrants" rel="nofollow">//cis.org/all-employment-growth-since-2000-went-to-immigrants</a></p>
<p>This &#8220;lesson plan&#8221; makes the same mistake made by most of the mainstream media on deportations. The large number of &#8220;deportations&#8221; attributed to the Obama Administration are people who are caught crossing the border and sent back, rather than already settled illegal immigrants being sent back. Under prior administrations those weren&#8217;t counted as &#8220;deportations.&#8221; In fact, under the Obama administration, settled illegal immigrants are very safe from deportaiton</p>
<p><a href="//www.latimes.com/changebrowser#url=/#section/-1/article/p2p-79794797/" rel="nofollow">//www.latimes.com/changebrowser#url=/#section/-1/article/p2p-79794797/</a></p>
<p>As are criminal aliens</p>
<p><a href="//cis.org/vaughan/lawsuit-career-ice-attorney-exposes-obama-anti-enforcement-campaign" rel="nofollow">//cis.org/vaughan/lawsuit-career-ice-attorney-exposes-obama-anti-enforcement-campaign</a></p>

		</div>
	</div><!-- #comment-## -->
	<div class="the-comment" id="comment-2097824">

		<div class="comment-meta">

			<span class="comment-author">Dave Gorak</span>
			<span class="comment-link">
				<a href="#comment-2097824" title="Comment Permalink">
					<span class="comment-date">December 10, 2014</span>
					<span class="comment-middot">&middot;</span>
					<span class="comment-time">3:27 pm</span>
				</a>
			</span>
		</div>
		<div class="comment-content" style="display:block;">

			<p>Let&#8217;s stop talking about what to do with the 11 million illegal aliens in this country.  What about the rest of us?  Eighteen million Americans can&#8217;t find full-time work, and the Obama Administration wants to give work permits and Social Security numbers to 5 million illegal workers who will then compete with our most vulnerable citizens in a dismal job market.  Why aren&#8217;t amnesty advocates in and out of Congress, including the media, addressing this very simple question?</p>

		</div>
	</div><!-- #comment-## -->
	<div class="the-comment alt" id="comment-2097957">

		<div class="comment-meta">

			<span class="comment-author">D Flinchum</span>
			<span class="comment-link">
				<a href="#comment-2097957" title="Comment Permalink">
					<span class="comment-date">December 10, 2014</span>
					<span class="comment-middot">&middot;</span>
					<span class="comment-time">5:00 pm</span>
				</a>
			</span>
		</div>
		<div class="comment-content" style="display:block;">

			<p>Why not start out with a question about the law of supply and demand?</p>
<p>The law of supply and demand notes that a large supply of any item or commodity, including workers, lowers its price. Isn&#8217;t it likely that the on-going depression of wages in the US is directly related to the massive number of both legal &#038; illegal immigrants that have entered the US in the last 15 years? What is the likely effect of Obama&#8217;s adding even more work permits to about 5 million (or more) illegal aliens on current un/underemployment levels?</p>
<p>The parties most assisted by massive immigration are the immigrants themselves (the wages) and the people who own the businesses they work for. In view of the fact that depressed wages likely contribute to the enrichment of the capital-owning upper 1-10%, isn&#8217;t it hypocritical of the the Democratic Party to moan about inequality in the US today when they are the leading architects of this cause of inequality by depressing wages through refusing to enforce immigration law and deport illegal aliens?</p>
<p>We are now learning that ObamaCare was enacted largely by the administration and its &#8216;consultants&#8217; deceiving the people, aka Grubering them. Isn&#8217;t it also likely that all of the supposed &#8216;benefits&#8217; that US workers are to receive as a result of allowing Obama&#8217;s amnesty via fiat is also deceitful? Are we again being Grubered? </p>
<p>Let&#8217;s ask these questions, shall we?</p>

		</div>
	</div><!-- #comment-## -->
